Activities  marking  the  55th Founder’s  Day   of  Melototah  Church   of  Zion  will begin today  at 5.30 pm. It will feature  seminars, lectures, prayer, deliverance, visit  to motherless babies’ homes with thanksgiving  on Sunday. Programme Co-ordinator,  Apostle  Lere  Julius  said: ’’This  year’s  edition promises to be eventful   as we  offer  prayers  to usher in  a new  government  through   the ballot. We   pray  for divine  wisdom  for our leaders  to pilot  affairs  of the country  and favour  for our members’’. The programme  takes  place  in  the  church auditorium, 18, Ikale  Street, Papa-Ajao,  Mushin. Time is 8. am  on Sunday.